| `job_queue.py:16-18` | Moved `await asyncio.sleep(0.01)` to *after* `job["status"] = "processing"` | TOCTOU race — all 5 workers saw the same job as "pending" during the sleep and all claimed it |
| `worker.py:17` | Added `queue.fail(job["id"], str(e))` in the exception handler | Exception handler only printed the error, never called `queue.fail()`, so jobs stayed in "processing" limbo |
